                        div.fragment#fragment_party
                            img.fragment__image(src="../img/section_services/party_photo.jpeg" alt="Party photo")
                            div.fragment__info
                                h3.fragment__title Opt For A Lip Stain
                                p.fragment__description Cream Blush-I am a firm believer that less is more…especially with cream products. Because of its consistency, it is the nature of cream blush to move on the face. One way to prevent this from happening is to apply a dusting of sheer loose powder over the cheeks after you have applied the blush to keep it where it belongs-on your cheeks.
                                a.fragment__link(href="#") Learn More #[span.fragment__arrow &rarr;]
                        div.fragment#fragment_beauty-box
                            img.fragment__image(src="../img/section_services/beauty-box_photo.jpeg" alt=" Beauty box photo")
                            div.fragment__info
                                h3.fragment__title Use A Mattifying Sunscreen
                                p.fragment__description Eyeliner-Eyeliner smudges by nature, but tends to look sexier when slightly imperfect. Rather than using black, which can look harsh, I often recommend trying navy blue.
                                a.fragment__link(href="#") Learn More #[span.fragment__arrow &rarr;]
                        div.fragment#fragment_course
                            img.fragment__image(src="../img/section_services/course_photo.jpg" alt="Course photo")
                            div.fragment__info
                                h3.fragment__title Choose The Right Primer For Your Skin
                                p.fragment__description Lipstick/Lip Gloss-There are products on the market made specifically to prevent feathering, and a secret trick of mine that I always use if I don’t have my Lip Glossing/No Feather Pencil on me is to dab foundation on your fingertip and smooth it over your lip line. This smooths out any lines around the mouth and provides an even surface for lip color to adhere…and stick to.
